WEBVTT

00:06.840 --> 00:09.274
<i>Previously on the affair...</i>

00:09.309 --> 00:11.142
Welcome to the end of the world.

00:11.177 --> 00:12.521
<i>Do you remember
the first time you saw her?</i>

00:12.545 --> 00:14.279
<i>Like it was yesterday.</i>

00:14.314 --> 00:15.747
I'm noah, by the way.

00:15.782 --> 00:16.848
What are we talking about?

00:16.883 --> 00:18.116
Noah's new book.

00:18.151 --> 00:19.417
Great. I didn't know.

00:19.452 --> 00:20.285
There was enough
to talk about yet.

00:20.320 --> 00:21.786
<i>Well,</i>

00:21.821 --> 00:22.999
<i>I haven't really gotten
too far with it.</i>

00:23.023 --> 00:24.023
<i>Is she flirting with you?</i>

00:24.057 --> 00:25.297
Do you want to get out of here?

00:26.393 --> 00:28.493
I don't want to divorce you,
you asshole!

00:28.528 --> 00:30.495
What... what do you want?

00:30.530 --> 00:32.997
I want you to come home.

00:33.033 --> 00:34.299
<i>It's extraordinary.</i>

00:34.334 --> 00:36.200
I want it in stores
by next fall.

00:36.236 --> 00:37.602
<i>I don't want this life.</i>

00:37.637 --> 00:39.437
<i>I have to leave.</i>

00:39.472 --> 00:40.805
<i>I'm in love with someone else.</i>

00:40.840 --> 00:42.140
You have chosen to divorce.

00:42.175 --> 00:44.676
In what I like to call
a humane way.

00:44.711 --> 00:46.844
<i>I blew up my life
for you, alison.</i>

00:46.880 --> 00:48.012
I don't belong to you.

00:48.048 --> 00:49.013
We're not living in your book.

00:49.049 --> 00:51.015
You can't... Control me.

00:55.055 --> 00:56.321
I'm pregnant.

00:58.091 --> 00:59.857
I don't know
who joanie's father is.

00:59.893 --> 01:01.659
I never want to see you again.

01:01.695 --> 01:03.528
And I thought
she had done it deliberately.

01:03.563 --> 01:06.965
<i>To trap me, make sure
I could never go back to you.</i>

01:13.206 --> 01:14.206
Fuck!

01:15.875 --> 01:16.908
It was a deer.

01:16.943 --> 01:18.509
It was a deer!

01:22.382 --> 01:23.748
Alison, if I don't do something,

01:23.783 --> 01:25.249
They're gonna convict me.

01:25.285 --> 01:27.552
<i>I know, just...
Just tell the truth.</i>

01:27.587 --> 01:29.354
Your honor,

01:29.389 --> 01:30.989
I'm guilty.
I killed scott lockhart.

01:31.024 --> 01:33.324
What the hell are you doing?
Sit down.

01:35.000 --> 01:41.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:50.530 --> 03:52.196
Ready to go?

04:31.771 --> 04:33.504
Hey.

04:33.540 --> 04:36.507
Hi. Hey.

04:56.429 --> 04:58.396
How are you feeling?

05:01.100 --> 05:02.900
I'm fine.

05:14.514 --> 05:17.148
Thou preparest a table before me.

05:17.183 --> 05:19.951
In the presence of mine enemies.

05:19.986 --> 05:22.653
Thou anointest my head with oil.

05:22.689 --> 05:25.122
My cup runneth over.

05:25.158 --> 05:28.259
Surely goodness and mercy
shall follow me.

05:28.294 --> 05:30.428
All the days of my life,

05:30.463 --> 05:33.731
And I will dwell in the house
of the lord forever.

05:35.435 --> 05:37.602
We will conclude
our service with a eulogy.

05:37.637 --> 05:39.503
I now invite arthur's son,

05:39.539 --> 05:41.105
Noah solloway,

05:41.140 --> 05:44.742
To share some remembrances
of his beloved father.

05:55.955 --> 05:57.355
Um...

06:07.800 --> 06:09.767
Those of you who knew my dad
will... will know.

06:09.802 --> 06:12.637
That we didn't always
get along so well.

06:15.875 --> 06:17.875
But I-i loved him.

06:20.647 --> 06:22.847
I did love him.

06:22.882 --> 06:26.517
Wh-when I was a boy...

06:26.552 --> 06:28.519
He used to take me fishing
in the... in the lake.

06:28.554 --> 06:32.123
Behind the house
where we grew up, and...

06:39.165 --> 06:41.966
Well,
we both really enjoyed that.

06:42.001 --> 06:44.302
My sister was...

06:46.339 --> 06:47.705
She and my dad were very close.

06:47.740 --> 06:52.410
I think she was...
She was more his type.

06:54.447 --> 06:55.680
But then she left.

06:55.715 --> 06:56.715
Heh.

07:07.560 --> 07:09.160
That was a hard time.

07:11.464 --> 07:13.731
That was a hard time.

07:13.766 --> 07:16.500
He had a... he had a hard life.
At least I think he did.

07:16.536 --> 07:19.904
To be... to be honest,
I-i never really knew him.

07:22.375 --> 07:24.175
Um...

07:27.480 --> 07:29.113
I always wanted to ask
more questions.

07:29.148 --> 07:31.015
You always think
there's gonna be...

07:31.050 --> 07:35.019
more time, but...

07:53.172 --> 07:54.972
Thank you for coming.

07:59.412 --> 08:03.414
Thank you, mr. Solloway,
for those, um, words.

08:03.449 --> 08:06.751
We will now conclude our service
by singing, at his request,

08:06.786 --> 08:08.753
Arthur's favorite song,

08:08.788 --> 08:11.756
"take me out to the ball game."

08:13.292 --> 08:14.959
Thank you for telling
that story, estelle.

08:14.994 --> 08:16.227
It was beautiful.

08:21.033 --> 08:22.600
I'm sorry.

08:22.635 --> 08:25.269
What is the matter with you?

08:25.304 --> 08:27.271
Nothing.

08:27.306 --> 08:28.973
Hey, there's your dad.

08:29.008 --> 08:30.474
Hey.

08:30.510 --> 08:32.176
Hey. Thanks for coming.

08:32.211 --> 08:34.278
I think granddad
would have liked that.

08:34.313 --> 08:36.447
Short and sweet. No bullshit.

08:36.482 --> 08:38.448
Hel... helen,
thank you so much for coming.

08:38.484 --> 08:39.750
You didn't have to do that.

08:39.785 --> 08:41.419
Well, I knew your father
for 30 years,

08:41.453 --> 08:43.254
And you know, where else
would I be?

08:43.289 --> 08:45.289
Can I talk to you for a second?

08:48.394 --> 08:50.161
Come here, sweetie.

08:54.167 --> 08:55.800
You haven't returned
any of my calls.

08:55.835 --> 08:56.634
I know.

08:56.669 --> 08:58.803
Why not?

08:58.838 --> 08:59.703
I don't know.

08:59.739 --> 09:01.372
I... we need to talk.

09:01.407 --> 09:03.174
About what?
About what we're doing.

09:03.209 --> 09:05.743
About what our new arrangement's
going to be.

09:08.648 --> 09:09.858
Are you still living
at your sister's?

09:09.882 --> 09:10.714
Yes.

09:10.750 --> 09:11.549
Well, will you be getting.

09:11.584 --> 09:12.383
A place of your own?

09:12.418 --> 09:13.784
Eventually.

09:13.820 --> 09:14.863
Do... i don't...
Don't you want someplace.

09:14.887 --> 09:16.387
Where you can be with the kids?

09:16.422 --> 09:18.456
They can come to nina's.
I mean alone.

09:18.491 --> 09:20.202
I don't think they want
to be alone with me.

09:20.226 --> 09:22.293
That's ridiculous.
You're their father.

09:22.328 --> 09:24.495
Stacey's afraid of me.
She's not afraid of you.

09:24.530 --> 09:27.531
She's uncomfortable 'cause she
hasn't seen you in three years.

09:27.567 --> 09:31.001
That's why you need
to spend time with her.

09:31.037 --> 09:32.636
Okay, I'm trying. I swear I am.

09:32.672 --> 09:34.071
It's just... it's... it's been...

09:34.106 --> 09:35.306
It's been two months.

09:35.341 --> 09:37.508
Just give me a break, will ya?

09:44.450 --> 09:45.983
Um...

09:47.720 --> 09:49.887
What about us?

09:51.557 --> 09:52.857
What about us?

10:01.567 --> 10:03.100
Excuse me.

10:03.135 --> 10:03.934
Here.

10:03.970 --> 10:05.703
We got it.

10:11.244 --> 10:14.845
"Everyone the father gives to me
will come to me."

10:14.881 --> 10:18.349
I will never turn away
anyone who believes in me.

10:18.384 --> 10:20.351
He who raised Jesus christ
from the dead.

10:20.386 --> 10:22.720
Will also give new life
to our mortal bodies.

10:22.755 --> 10:24.221
Through his indwelling spirit.

10:25.591 --> 10:27.525
My heart, therefore, is glad,

10:27.560 --> 10:30.528
And my spirit rejoices.

10:30.563 --> 10:33.964
My body also shall rest in hope.

10:34.000 --> 10:36.433
You will show me
the path of life.

10:36.469 --> 10:39.136
In your presence
there is fullness of joy,

10:39.171 --> 10:42.706
"And in your right hand
are pleasures forevermore."

10:46.145 --> 10:48.579
noah!

10:48.614 --> 10:50.080
Noah!

10:55.354 --> 10:56.354
Noah!

11:05.698 --> 11:07.342
"The lord lift up
his countenance upon him.

11:07.366 --> 11:09.166
And give him peace."

11:09.201 --> 11:10.134
Amen.

11:10.169 --> 11:12.603
Amen.

11:12.638 --> 11:14.038
Amen.

11:39.732 --> 11:41.699
Thank you so much for coming.

11:49.075 --> 11:50.441
Thanks. Yes, of course.

11:50.476 --> 11:53.010
Thank you.

11:53.045 --> 11:54.011
You okay?

11:54.046 --> 11:55.813
That was a lovely service, nina.

11:55.848 --> 11:58.349
Your father would be pleased.
Thanks.

11:58.384 --> 12:00.362
You're coming back to the house,
though, aren't you?

12:00.386 --> 12:01.952
I don't know.

12:01.988 --> 12:03.687
Come on.

12:03.723 --> 12:05.689
The kids, they haven't
seen each other in forever.

12:05.725 --> 12:07.224
Mine are so looking forward
to it.

12:07.259 --> 12:09.693
Do you think we should
come back to the house?

12:09.729 --> 12:11.228
Only if you want to.

12:16.702 --> 12:18.669
It's a school night, so...

12:18.704 --> 12:21.505
right.

12:21.540 --> 12:23.040
This one time.

12:23.075 --> 12:24.341
Their grandfather just died.

12:24.377 --> 12:25.809
The... the kids
should be together.

12:25.845 --> 12:27.511
Nina, she gave her answer.

12:29.949 --> 12:32.349
We should go. Okay.

12:32.385 --> 12:34.429
Martin needs more time
with his homework this semester.

12:34.453 --> 12:36.353
Because he's been coming home
with cs and ds,

12:36.389 --> 12:38.055
And if he fails out
of another school,

12:38.090 --> 12:39.757
He won't get into college.

12:39.792 --> 12:40.824
Thank you for coming.

12:40.860 --> 12:42.092
Helen.

12:42.128 --> 12:43.927
It was good to see you.

12:47.433 --> 12:48.899
His adviser wants to have.

12:48.934 --> 12:50.345
A parent-teacher conference
next week.

12:50.369 --> 12:52.903
I think you should be there too.

12:52.938 --> 12:54.938
When is it?

12:56.542 --> 12:58.542
It's thursday at four.

12:59.745 --> 13:01.211
Okay, I'll try.

13:07.787 --> 13:09.286
Let's go, mom.

13:09.321 --> 13:12.856
Martin, come and say good-bye
to your father.

13:12.892 --> 13:14.124
Martin, did you hear me?

13:14.160 --> 13:15.893
I said, "come and say
good-bye to your... ".

13:15.928 --> 13:17.895
Don't make him, helen. Please.

13:48.627 --> 13:50.894
You have a lovely home.

13:50.930 --> 13:52.062
Thank you.

13:52.098 --> 13:54.431
It's not mine.

13:54.467 --> 13:57.501
You're not the husband?

13:57.536 --> 13:59.770
I'm sorry, whose husband?

13:59.805 --> 14:01.739
I thought you were
nina's husband.

14:01.774 --> 14:03.807
No, no, no. I'm the brother.

14:03.843 --> 14:06.477
The brother.

14:06.512 --> 14:08.679
The brother who went to prison?

14:10.649 --> 14:12.616
You killed him, you know,

14:12.651 --> 14:14.952
With your antics.

14:14.987 --> 14:18.155
He died of a broken heart.

14:18.190 --> 14:19.990
I thought he died of emphysema.

14:20.025 --> 14:22.092
You're a horror.

14:22.128 --> 14:23.994
Excuse me, donna.

14:24.029 --> 14:26.597
I hope you don't mind terribly.
I'm gonna steal my brother.

14:26.632 --> 14:28.098
Where you going?

14:28.134 --> 14:31.101
To grieve.

14:31.137 --> 14:32.137
Come on.

14:37.376 --> 14:38.376
Here.

14:50.489 --> 14:52.489
Muscle relaxants.

15:04.370 --> 15:06.470
How was teaching this week?

15:06.505 --> 15:08.038
It was fine.

15:08.073 --> 15:09.973
You have any fun?

15:10.009 --> 15:11.208
Not really.

15:12.945 --> 15:15.712
That's not the point, is it?
The point is to have a job.

15:15.748 --> 15:18.849
Well, if they like you,

15:18.884 --> 15:21.051
Then... Maybe they'll give you.

15:21.086 --> 15:23.654
A full-time gig
at the end of the semester.

15:23.689 --> 15:25.022
Maybe.

15:27.860 --> 15:29.593
You should really
shave that beard.

15:29.628 --> 15:30.628
You look insane.

15:34.567 --> 15:37.367
Noah, it's a good university,

15:37.403 --> 15:38.869
And you're a convict.

15:38.904 --> 15:40.304
Ex-convict.

15:42.041 --> 15:44.441
Don't you think
that's part of the appeal?

15:50.816 --> 15:53.784
I'm sorry, I'm just...

15:53.819 --> 15:55.586
I'm having a hard time.

15:55.621 --> 15:59.423
Of course you're having
a hard time.

15:59.458 --> 16:02.960
But it's... it's going
to get better.

16:02.995 --> 16:04.127
You just have to stay...

16:04.163 --> 16:05.729
Alive?

16:05.764 --> 16:07.965
I was going to say "positive."

16:17.476 --> 16:19.910
I think jp's tired of
having me around.

16:19.945 --> 16:21.979
Forget jp. I'll take care of it.

16:22.014 --> 16:24.414
He's just tired in general.

16:24.450 --> 16:26.650
It's just been a long summer.

16:34.793 --> 16:38.362
You know, you're the only one
who's every forgiven me, nin.

16:41.467 --> 16:43.467
<i>Well, you forgave me once.</i>

16:43.502 --> 16:46.136
For something
pretty awful, so...

16:51.810 --> 16:54.011
Besides,
I think you're innocent.

16:59.718 --> 17:01.551
I'm not.

18:14.026 --> 18:15.170
<i>How could he never mention it?</i>

18:15.194 --> 18:16.493
<i>What?</i>

18:16.528 --> 18:17.861
<i>You should have asked him.</i>

18:17.896 --> 18:19.563
<i>What is the matter with you?</i>

18:19.598 --> 18:20.742
<i>I would have never
asked him that.</i>

18:20.766 --> 18:22.265
<i>Just calm down.</i>

18:22.301 --> 18:24.401
<i>We're gonna figure it out, okay?</i>

18:24.436 --> 18:26.937
<i>What do you think
we're gonna do, nina?</i>

18:26.972 --> 18:29.039
<i>How do you think we're
gonna pay for this trip?</i>

18:29.074 --> 18:30.574
<i>And for christmas?</i>

18:30.609 --> 18:32.209
<i>It's got to be
some kind of joke.</i>

18:32.244 --> 18:34.745
<i>Your brother?
Your fucking brother?</i>

18:37.883 --> 18:39.483
Everything okay?

18:42.221 --> 18:44.788
Your father's will arrived
this morning.

18:51.630 --> 18:52.896
Okay.

18:55.434 --> 18:57.434
He didn't have much to leave.

18:59.304 --> 19:01.605
He had his house...

19:01.640 --> 19:04.041
Which he left to you.

19:04.076 --> 19:05.275
To me?

19:07.079 --> 19:08.278
Why?

19:08.313 --> 19:09.880
I don't know, noah.

19:09.915 --> 19:11.915
Why don't you tell us?

19:13.452 --> 19:15.452
I don't know either.

19:16.755 --> 19:18.255
You know he hated you?

19:18.290 --> 19:20.724
Jp. No, no, no.

19:20.759 --> 19:24.561
He could barely talk about you.

19:24.596 --> 19:26.129
She's the one.

19:26.165 --> 19:27.931
Who went to see him
every sunday.

19:27.966 --> 19:29.433
She took him to church.

19:29.468 --> 19:31.234
She took him to the doctor's.

19:31.270 --> 19:32.903
She changed his oxygen.

19:32.938 --> 19:36.139
She changed his fuckin' diapers.

19:36.175 --> 19:39.509
You know that we had to pay
for a live-in nurse at the end?

19:40.679 --> 19:41.912
We're in something of a hole.

19:41.947 --> 19:42.746
Here at the moment.

19:42.781 --> 19:43.647
Doesn't matter.

19:43.682 --> 19:44.481
It doesn't?

19:44.516 --> 19:45.916
And why's that?

19:45.951 --> 19:47.918
Because you planted a money tree
in the backyard,

19:47.953 --> 19:50.320
And we can just go out
and pick some fucking bills?

19:50.355 --> 19:51.154
You're embarrassing me.

19:51.190 --> 19:52.489
I am?

19:52.524 --> 19:54.624
Has he even paid
for groceries once?

19:54.660 --> 19:56.159
Once since he's been here?

19:56.195 --> 19:58.261
Just go take a walk, please.

19:58.297 --> 20:00.130
He's just like
your fuckin' father.

20:00.165 --> 20:01.698
Get out!

20:07.539 --> 20:09.806
We needed that house, nina.

20:15.481 --> 20:18.148
We needed it.

20:18.183 --> 20:21.318
Fuck it.

20:25.891 --> 20:26.790
Here, let me.

20:26.825 --> 20:28.658
No, I got it.

20:28.694 --> 20:30.560
I got it.

20:44.042 --> 20:45.642
I'll pick you up at six.

20:45.677 --> 20:47.878
No, I told you, I'll...

20:47.913 --> 20:49.045
I'll find my own place.

20:49.081 --> 20:50.514
You have no money.

20:50.549 --> 20:52.149
I have a little.

20:52.184 --> 20:53.250
I'll manage.

20:53.285 --> 20:56.253
Just... Let me talk to jp, okay?

20:56.288 --> 20:57.320
He will calm down.

20:57.356 --> 20:59.556
I don't want the house.

21:02.261 --> 21:04.094
Just tell jp he can have it.

21:04.129 --> 21:05.562
He can sell it. I don't care.

21:05.597 --> 21:08.031
He can't have it.
Dad left it to you.

21:08.066 --> 21:10.767
I'm never going back there,
nina.

21:10.802 --> 21:12.435
You know that.

21:14.306 --> 21:16.540
He was trying to apologize.

21:16.575 --> 21:18.542
Yeah, well,
it's too late for that.

21:20.045 --> 21:21.045
Fuckhead.

21:22.114 --> 21:24.714
It's way too late for that.

21:33.725 --> 21:35.692
"And so in the end,."

21:35.727 --> 21:37.894
As she watched him
get back into his car.

21:37.930 --> 21:40.597
And drive back
down the mountain,

21:40.632 --> 21:42.966
She couldn't help but wonder,

21:43.001 --> 21:45.402
Would she feel differently
in the morning?

21:45.437 --> 21:48.405
Would she wake up again
with that sense of possibility.

21:48.440 --> 21:51.808
That she'd taken for granted
as a girl?

21:51.843 --> 21:53.210
In other words,

21:53.245 --> 21:55.245
Is this moment the end
of her beginning.

21:55.280 --> 21:58.315
Or the beginning of her end?

21:58.350 --> 22:00.116
She was still
pondering the question.

22:00.152 --> 22:02.152
When she heard
the teakettle whistle.

22:02.187 --> 22:04.821
And turned from the window.

22:04.856 --> 22:08.091
"When she looked back again,
his car was gone."

22:09.861 --> 22:11.228
The end.

22:18.971 --> 22:21.905
Mr. Solloway?

22:21.940 --> 22:25.308
Yeah, th... thanks.
Thanks, audrey.

22:29.715 --> 22:31.715
Questions, comments, concerns?

22:39.558 --> 22:42.292
Charlette?

22:42.327 --> 22:44.761
I thought it was really elegant,
audrey.

22:44.796 --> 22:47.831
I liked the wind imagery.

22:47.866 --> 22:49.699
I felt your narrator's
excitement.

22:49.735 --> 22:51.968
When the weather patterns
changed unexpectedly.

22:57.476 --> 22:59.876
You don't agree, mr. Solloway?

23:01.513 --> 23:04.180
No, charlette, I don't.

23:04.216 --> 23:06.549
I thought it was very dull.

23:06.585 --> 23:08.285
Unless it was
supposed to be a satire.

23:08.320 --> 23:09.653
Was it?

23:11.523 --> 23:13.890
No. No, I didn't think it was.

23:13.925 --> 23:16.359
Unfortunately, all that audrey
has revealed here today.

23:16.395 --> 23:18.561
Is how shockingly unoriginal.

23:18.597 --> 23:20.363
Her inner life actually is.

23:20.399 --> 23:22.699
It would probably behoove you
to turn off your computer,

23:22.734 --> 23:24.801
Get off your couch,
and go outside.

